tCommittedPoint":null,"height":0,"link":null,"startArrowhead":null,"strokeColor":"#e5e7eb","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"endBinding":null,"versionNonce":801896772,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":727,"angle":0,"y":-3241,"width":522},{"seed":960725572,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"M4XCnIVNJbqDKh83ywnv8","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":14,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1772873306458,"locked":false,"text":"The most consequential calculation is the trie memory\nfootprint. 300M unique nodes at 128 bytes each equals\n38 GB of raw data per shard — but once you add\nindexes, bloom filters for fast misses, and top-K\nprecomputed lists at every internal node, this grows\nto ~200 GB per shard. With 5 shards and 3 replicas\neach, the cluster needs 15 trie service instances each\nloaded with ~200 GB in memory. This is the number\nthat determines your minimum hardware spec and forces\nyou into distributed sharding from day one.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b3w","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"The most consequential calculation is the trie memory\nfootprint. 300M unique nodes at 128 bytes each equals\n38 GB of raw data per shard — but once you add\nindexes, bloom filters for fast misses, and top-K\nprecomputed lists at every internal node, this grows\nto ~200 GB per shard. With 5 shards and 3 replicas\neach, the cluster needs 15 trie service instances each\nloaded with ~200 GB in memory. This is the number\nthat determines your minimum hardware spec and forces\nyou into distributed sharding from day one.","height":175,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#374151","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":2113809660,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":727,"angle":0,"y":-3229,"width":381.26153564453125},{"seed":1839372740,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"-mDV0_D6zHL-dXvchkq_l","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":18,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1772873306458,"locked":false,"text":"Peak vs Average","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b3x","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Peak vs Average","height":22.5,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":168046788,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":727,"angle":0,"y":-3053,"width":143.27993774414062},{"seed":87212356,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"nel-CRqgdD07DxMS7HO_f","strokeWidth":1,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"startBinding":null,"endArrowhead":null,"opacity":100,"updated":1772873306458,"locked":false,"points":[[0,0],[522,0]],"polygon":false,"version":5,"type":"line","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b3y","roundness":null,"lastCommittedPoint":null,"height":0,"link":null,"startArrowhead":null,"strokeColor":"#e5e7eb","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"endBinding":null,"versionNonce":740765052,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":727,"angle":0,"y":-3029,"width":522},{"seed":391248068,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"IT_SGeprXeBe6m3vu44is","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":14,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1772873306458,"locked":false,"text":"The 1.75x peak multiplier comes from traffic patterns:\naround 57% of daily searches happen in an 8-hour\nwindow (9am-5pm local time), concentrated further by\nlunch breaks and commute peaks. The true worst case\nis a viral news event during peak hours — a breaking\nstory can spike a single prefix (e.g. \"trump\", \"earthquake\")\nto 50x its normal load. The hot-prefix problem is why\nsharding by prefix range, not by consistent hash, is\nthe correct design for autocomplete systems.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b3z","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"The 1.75x peak multiplier comes from traffic patterns:\naround 57% of daily searches happen in an 8-hour\nwindow (9am-5pm local time), concentrated further by\nlunch breaks and commute peaks. The true worst case\nis a viral news event during peak hours — a breaking\nstory can spike a single prefix (e.g. \"trump\", \"earthquake\")\nto 50x its normal load. The hot-prefix problem is why\nsharding by prefix range, not by consistent hash, is\nthe correct design for autocomplete systems.","height":157.5,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#374151","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1867085892,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":727,"angle":0,"y":-3017,"width":393.21749877929688},{"seed":530464836,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"DumQcM2ngUT1jStQd_fiQ","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":18,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1772873306458,"locked":false,"text":"Storage Growth Rate","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b40","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Storage Growth Rate","height":22.5,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":509353468,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":727,"angle":0,"y":-2831,"width":191.73587036132812},{"seed":1979029444,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"66_-PE4KnTtCCW6VTRz1u","strokeWidth":1,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"startBinding":null,"endArrowhead":null,"opacity":100,"updated":1772873306458,"locked":false,"points":[[0,0],[522,0]],"polygon":false,"version":5,"type":"line","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b41","roundness":null,"lastCommittedPoint":null,"height":0,"link":null,"startArrowhead":null,"strokeColor":"#e5e7eb","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"endBinding":null,"versionNonce":460967876,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":727,"angle":0,"y":-2807,"width":522},{"seed":1182138180,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"woLKYtDjnW-JkOWoSr1A-","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":14,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1772873306458,"locked":false,"text":"2.5B new log events per day at ~128 bytes each adds\n~320 GB of raw log data daily. With 90-day retention\nfor trending signal computation, cold log storage grows\nto ~29 TB of logs alone — and with replication and\ncompressed Parquet archival it reaches ~2 PB total.\nThe active trie stays fixed around 10 TB total because\nold queries age out after 90 days. The key operational\ndecision is when to compact trie nodes: too frequent\ncompaction blocks reads; too infrequent lets stale\nsuggestions accumulate in hot prefix lists.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b42","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"2.5B new log events per day at ~128 bytes each adds\n~320 GB of raw log data daily. With 90-day retention\nfor trending signal computation, cold log storage grows\nto ~29 TB of logs alone — and with replication and\ncompressed Parquet archival it reaches ~2 PB total.\nThe active trie stays fixed around 10 TB total because\nold queries age out after 90 days. The key operational\ndecision is when to compact trie nodes: too frequent\ncompaction blocks reads; too infrequent lets stale\nsuggestions accumulate in hot prefix lists.","height":175,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#374151","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1302265468,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":727,"angle":0,"y":-2795,"width":388.75146484375},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#f59e0b","link":null,"roughness":1,"groupIds":[],"index":"b43","backgroundColor":"#fffbeb","angle":0,"fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":2,"version":5,"roundness":{"type":3},"type":"rectangle","updated":1772873306458,"id":"k23nSES6XiLTjD0-L7jpM","x":727,"seed":159217348,"boundElements":[],"y":-2551,"opacity":100,"height":110,"width":526,"frameId":null,"strokeStyle":"solid","versionNonce":515061572},{"seed":2074738244,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"33ek6b-YIs8LRfklTEj_N","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":14,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1772873306458,"locked":false,"text":"Key insight: The trie must live entirely in memory.\n200 GB per shard is the forcing function for distributed\narchitecture. Storage math is not academic here —\nit is the reason the system has 15+ instances\nrather than a single fast server.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b44","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Key insight: The trie must live entirely in memory.\n200 GB per shard is the forcing function for distributed\narchitecture. Storage math is not academic here —\nit is the reason the system has 15+ instances\nrather than a single fast server.","height":87.5,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#92400e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1118949116,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":743,"angle":0,"y":-2535,"width":392.92349243164062},{"seed":366581188,"strokeStyle":"dashed","id":"CYz8BDPdCpv5tfzS2IYAU","strokeWidth":1,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"startBinding":null,"endArrowhead":null,"opacity":100,"updated":1772873306458,"locked":false,"points":[[0,0],[1450,0]],"polygon":false,"version":5,"type":"line","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b45","roundness":null,"lastCommittedPoint":null,"height":0,"link":null,"startArrowhead":null,"strokeColor":"#9ca3af","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"endBinding":null,"versionNonce":1431547588,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-149,"angle":0,"y":-2381,"width":1450},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#6BA3D6","link":null,"roughness":1,"groupIds":[],"index":"b46","backgroundColor":"#6BA3D6","angle":0,"fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":2,"version":5,"roundness":null,"type":"ellipse","updated":1772873